modules.description: Provides functions for generating permutations, combinations, and Cartesian products of lists, with optimized traversal and memory usage. Works with native OCaml lists and arrays, supporting efficient iteration over large datasets. Used in algorithmic trading for scenario generation and in bioinformatics for sequence analysis.

Generates integer partitions, permutations, combinations, and sequences using iterator functions that yield arrays. Processes lists and integers to produce ordered and unordered selections with customizable constraints. Supports restricted sequences where each position draws from a distinct list of options.
